      "content": "that makes sense, very sleek. but what about people from places like india, or nigeria, or japan? if they show up to a big international meeting wearing traditional professional attire—like a high-quality silk sari, an agbada, or a formal kimono—how does that fit into this \"universal\" idea of sophistication? is that seen as professional, or is it more like a \"cultural outfit\" rather than business wear?",
